Mesua ferrea

   [7736.jpg]
    Authority   L.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Dilleniidae:Guttiferales:Guttiferae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 7736

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   A medium sized to tall evergreen tree reaching a height of 30-45 m or
   more. The trunk is often buttressed at the base and the crown is dense
   and conical.
   KILLING T
   Frost tolerant.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial, that produce fertile seeds at the age of 15-20 years.
   COMMON NAMES
   Mesua, Iron Wood tree, Nahor, Dieng-ngai, Ngai-ching, Nagkesar,
   Nagesar, Nageswar, Nagchampa, Nagakesara, Nagasampige, Nanga, Peri,
   Veluthapala, Churuli, Vainavu, Nagchampa, Nageshvaro, Nangu, Nangal,
   Suruli, Vainavu, Nageshvaro, Nangu, Nangal, Suruli, Nagachambagam,
   Nagkesara, Kesaramu, Nagachampakamum, Nageswar.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonyms: M. pedunculata, M. coromandeliana, M. speciosa, M.
   roxburghii, M. scerophylla, M. pulchella. Mesua occurs naturally in
   northern India, Bangladesh and northern Myanmar. In India, mesua can be
   found at elevations from 60 to 1500 m. It is found on well drained flat
   land and undulating and hilly country. It is adapted to a relative
   humidity of 80-100% in July and 60-80% in January.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Rashid M 1975 pp 239-262 [TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, DRA, PH, LIG, USE]
   Zabala N 1990 pp 66-67 [TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, DRA, DEP, FER, LIG, USE]

